north while huge doorways lead to more rooms to the east west and south.

The Giant's Treasury
    A deep rumbling noice echos throughout the entire room as you enter.
Glittering coffers and chests rest near the back wall of this place and
banners depicting giants in great battle hang from the walls of this
otherwise rather empty room.  It appears that this place is where the giants
of this village have stored the wealth that they have amassed over the years.

exit the room to the west.

Throne Room
    You are standing in the north side of the throne room. Thick wooden
beams span the ceiling that stands at least three times the height of a
tall man. Suspended from the beams are banners displaying the coat of arms
of various members of court, some new, and some so faded with age they can
hardly be made out. Tapestries cover the walls, depicting scenes of the
hunt, tourneys, and great battles. Between the tapestries stand wooden
benches covered with velvet pillows, where those waiting for audience may

wooden beams span the ceiling that stands at least three times the height

hunt, tourneys, and great battles. Between the tapestries stand wooden
benches covered with velvet pillows, where those waiting for audience may
sit and rest. In front of the bench in the east wall, you notice some
strange scuff marks on the floor. From here, the room extends to the south
and west.

upward. Sitting high above the center of the lake is a cloud, on top of

the clear blue skies, colorful pennants at their tops snapping in the stiff
breeze which seems to have no affect on the cloud itself.

City View

    You have finally climbed far enough up the mountain to clear the
treeline, and a marvelous vista spreads out before you. Looking east and
down you see a large valley. It is surrounded on all sides by more
mountains, their peaks covered with snow. On the slopes of the surrounding
mountains, above the level of the trees, are what appear to be many small
farms. At the bottom of the valley is a large lake, formed by snowmelt,
which is the source of the stream you were following. On the west shore of
the lake is a village, looking tiny in the distance, and you can see smoke
rising from some of the chimneys of the homes there. But that sight does
little more than hold your attention for a moment, for your eyes are drawn
upward. Sitting high above the center of the lake is a cloud, on top of
which is one of the largest castles you have seen, its towers rising into
the clear blue skies, colorful pennants at their tops snapping in the stiff
breeze which seems to have no affect on the cloud itself.

City View

    You have finally climbed far enough up the mountain to clear the
treeline, and a marvelous vista spreads out before you. Looking east and
down you see a large valley. It is surrounded on all sides by more
mountains, their peaks covered with snow. On the slopes of the surrounding
mountains, above the level of the trees, are what appear to be many small
farms. At the bottom of the valley is a large lake, formed by snowmelt,
which is the source of the stream you were following. On the west shore of
the lake is a village, looking tiny in the distance, and you can see smoke
rising from some of the chimneys of the homes there. But that sight does
little more than hold your attention for a moment, for your eyes are drawn
upward. Sitting high above the center of the lake is a cloud, on top of
which is one of the largest castles you have seen, its towers rising into
the clear blue skies, colorful pennants at their tops snapping in the stiff
breeze which seems to have no affect on the cloud itself.
